OL,7,FKane, from Coolshinney Heights in
OL,8,FMagherafelt, and Kelly, of Edmund
OL,9,FCourt in Tobermore, were charged with
OL,10,Fthe same offence.
OL,12,FFootage of the singing, which involved
OL,13,Fmembers of the flute band punching the
OL,14,Fair, was played in court.
OL,16,FProsecutors argued that the lyrics,
OL,17,Fincluding references to Ms McAreavy
OL,18,Fbeing "hammered and beaten about by
OL,19,Fstrangers" were about mocking the
OL,20,Fmurder of a young Catholic woman in a
OL,21,Fvenue surrounded by Union flags.
