OL,7,F"The words used can only be regarded
OL,8,Fby any right-minded person as
OL,9,Fabhorrent," a Crown lawyer said.
OL,11,F"The only reasonable inference is that
OL,12,Fthe intent was to incite hatred."
OL,14,FKelly declined to give evidence at the
OL,15,Fhearing, but during police interviews
OL,16,Fhe denied taking part in the singing.
OL,18,FHis solicitor, Richard Monteith, also
OL,19,Fargued that the lyrics made no
OL,20,Freference to Ms McAreavey's religion.
